    "created_at": "2012-12-05T19:56:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-12-05T19:56:54Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Before I adress this, I should point out that the docs claim this type of thing is [highly un-recommended](http://docs.python.org/2/library/user.html).\n\nAnyway, I can't reproduce this in Ubuntu 12.04 unless I launch `iptest` as `PYTHONSTARTUP=$HOME/.pythonrc.py iptest ...`.\n\nAt this point, you've discovered an easy fix.  Just launch iptest as:\n\n```\n$ PYTHONSTARTUP=\"\" iptest ...\n```\n\nTo clarify, do you think we should be overriding this environment variable in `iptest`?\n"
  },
