    "created_at": "2012-12-05T20:11:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-12-05T20:11:03Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "The advice on that page refers to the user module, which is only somewhat related. The PYTHONSTARTUP environment variable is not deprecated, only takes effect in interactive sessions, and is the standard way to customize the interactive interpreter.\n\nYes, since the ipython tests are intending to test interactions with the interactive interpreter itself, I think the environment variable should be overridden in iptest. This would make the passing and failure of tests independent of the user's private configuration.\n"
  },
