    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Rather than overriding variables, I think we should call Python with [the -E flag](http://docs.python.org/3/using/cmdline.html#cmdoption-E) to ignore them. But why is `PYTHONSTARTUP` being used anyway? The docs say that's only used for the Python interactive prompt, and a quick experiment supports that. We don't refer to PYTHONSTARTUP anywhere in the IPython code.\n"
